The Competition Commission says food prices are stabilising compared to the early days of lockdown. The commission received numerous complaints of price increases for essential food. To discuss this, we are joined on Skype by Deputy Commissioner, Hardin Ratshisusu. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Competition Commission says food prices are stabilising compared to the early days of lockdown. The commission received numerous complaints of price increases for essential food. READ: Cost of household food basket rising Deputy Commissioner Hardin Ratshisusu said they picked up a trend of price increases, particularly on basic foodstuffs. "We found that early on, around March/April, prices of basic foodstuffs increased. Vegetables, basic spices, garlic, as well as, other essentials. READ: Competition Commission says food prices expected to fall "We then thought it's best to analyse the trends and see what is actually happening out there." Ratshisusu said panic buying and predatory practices by businesses trying to profit from the pandemic prompted the initial hike, but stated prices have now begun to stabilise. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.